6. The failure of our first overseas campaign in Norway confirmed my opinion of the para- mount importance of the Anti-Aircraft defences; if we could obtain. mastery in the air, there would be no invasion; if we could not, no ex- peditionary force could be launched from the United Kingdom. I therefore pressed for and secured a large expansion of our Anti-Aircraft defences during 1940.
